</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E8403669FF8AFFF6FF591E19878BB679" blockId="29.[160,1155,1044,1138]" pageId="29" pageNumber="828">
This species is reported from throughout the Americas, including the West Indies (
<bibRefCitation id="8C6E4B98FF8AFFF6FBDF1E198446B65B" author="Balke M &amp; Hajek J &amp; Hendrich L" pageId="29" pageNumber="828" pagination="91 - 100" refId="ref22236" refString="Balke M, Hajek J, Hendrich L. 2017. Generic reclassification of species formerly included in Rhantus Dejean (Coleoptera, Dytiscidae, Colymbetinae). Zootaxa. 4258 (1): 91 - 100. doi: 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4258.1.7." type="journal article" year="2017">Balke et al. 2017</bibRefCitation>
). We found this genus commonly in deep quiet pools in ghuts, and in marginal vegetation of ponds and pools all over St. Thomas.
</paragraph>
